Start, Fresh ‚Äî Redesigning the Windows Start menu for you - Microsoft Design

Windows ‚Äì UX/UI Start, Fresh ‚Äî Redesigning the Windows Start menu for you This is the first post in our new Beyond the Surface series, a behind-the-scenes look at how craft comes to life in Windows products and features. By The Windows Design team May 9, 2025 ‚Äì The estimated reading time is 5 min. A quiet moment of d√©j√†‚ÄØvu Think back to the very first time you pressed Start.
Maybe you were nine, borrowing your mum‚Äôs laptop to play Minesweeper.
Maybe you were twenty-three, racing against a deadline and hunting for PowerPoint.
In that single click lived a promise: everything you need, right here, ready when you are. Thirty years later the promise remains, but the world around it hums at a new tempo. Phones flicker, tasks blur, screens multiply. So, we asked ourselves: How do we keep that original promise and let it breathe in 2025? The answer arrives today in a refreshed Start menu that is lighter on its feet, warmer to the touch, and‚Äîabove all‚Äîyours. Our journey echoes the wider Windows 11 philosophy of calm, human-centered technology. The spark Great design usually begins with a whisper, not a thunderclap.
Over coffee chats, Feedback Hub notes, and thousands of remote interviews, we heard the same refrain: ‚ÄúHelp me find my apps faster. Let me bend Start to fit the way I work. And please‚Äîkeep the magic, don‚Äôt lose the soul.‚Äù Those voices lit the path ahead, inspiring our design decisions. Four guiding stars Apps, at a glance
Your entire library‚Äîpinned, installed, or freshly discovered‚Äîshould be right there. Make it yours
Start should feel like it grew up on your desk, featuring only what and how much you want. Accelerate the day
Every pixel must earn its keep, shaving seconds off routine actions so creativity gets a head start. Honor the icon
Respect three decades of muscle memory. Update, don‚Äôt upend. The craft journey From net new features to redesigns like the Start menu, every Windows design journey is deeply rooted in craft and follows three key steps: Explore Whiteboards, Figma frames, floor-to-ceiling paper prototypes‚Äînothing was too scrappy. We sketched out a plethora of layouts, letting ourselves go wild and discover new things before applying the editorial pen. Validate Over 300 Windows 11 fans joined unmoderated studies and dozens more hopped into live co-creation calls. We watched eye-tracking heat maps swirl, counted scroll wheels, and listened for ‚Äúoh!‚Äùs of delight to know where we were hitting the mark. Refine You asked for‚Ä¶
We built‚Ä¶ Easier app discovery
All apps brought up to the top level, in three views, including a category grid view that prioritizes your most used apps‚Äîreminiscent of your phone, no more marathon scrolling. Smarter suggestions
Recommendations made just for you that learn in real time and a way to hide them if you don‚Äôt find them helpful. More control
Quick switches to show ‚ÄúMore pins‚Äù, ‚ÄúMore recommendations‚Äù, or a perfectly balanced mix. Clear mobile separation
A slim ‚Äúphone sliver‚Äù that glides in from the edge‚Äîthere when you need it, gone when you don‚Äôt. We tested and tweaked the design on a huge range of devices until the menu felt like it belonged on both a Surface Go and a 49-inch ultrawide. We sweated every pixel to make sure it needed to be there and to ensure the experience was filled with grace and ease. The final experience: a fresh Start Dynamic recommendations Files and apps surface exactly when they matter‚Äîyesterday‚Äôs missed meeting recording at 9 am, snap groups to get you back in the flow throughout the day, that app you always open around 2 pm, the app you didn‚Äôt know you needed just when you need it. More and better views for all‚ÄØapps No more digging to find your apps! They now live at the top level now and you can choose between logical categories, a neat grid, or the familiar A-Z list. Each is effortless to skim and scroll wheel friendly. Mobile content, gently blended Pick up a WhatsApp photo or a to-do from your Android phone without losing desktop flow. Keep on top of the latest messages from your iPhone. The phone panel attached to the Start menu respects screen real estate‚Äîand your attention span. Personalization, elevated Expand the section you use most; collapse or completely hide the ones you don‚Äôt. Pin your most used apps, set the all-apps view you prefer. Start makes better use of your screen real estate by being bigger on big screens and more compact on smaller ones. Under-the-hood speed We‚Äôre keeping the promise of Start being the accelerator of your day by making it load in a snap, so you won‚Äôt be dragged by lag. Looking forward Design is a conversation, not a monologue. Yesterday we listened with all ears, today we speak with pixels; tomorrow we‚Äôll take our turn and listen again. Install the latest Windows build, click that familiar logo, and let us know what sings‚Äîor what still needs tuning. Together we‚Äôll keep the promise of Start alive: everything you need, right here, ready when you are. Thank you for beginning (again) with Start. Title: Trezor Suite: Manage Your Crypto with Security and Ease
HTML: Trezor Suite: A Complete Platform for Safer Crypto Management Note: This is an independent educational page and is not affiliated with or endorsed by SatoshiLabs (Trezor). The Trezor Suite is the official software application designed to work hand in hand with your Trezor hardware wallet. Available as both a desktop app and a secure web version, it provides a unified interface for sending, receiving, and managing cryptocurrencies safely. Whether you‚Äôre storing Bitcoin long-term, managing Ethereum tokens, or checking portfolio balances, Trezor Suite brings security and usability together in one place. What Is Trezor Suite? Trezor Suite is the central hub for all your crypto operations with a Trezor hardware wallet. Instead of relying on third-party software, you can interact with your assets through this official interface built by SatoshiLabs. It combines strong security, user-friendly design, and regular updates to help protect your investments and streamline your experience. Trezor Suite is available on Windows, macOS, and Linux, with a browser-based option for quick access. The desktop version is generally recommended for maximum protection against phishing and malicious extensions. Key Features of Trezor Suite Secure crypto management: Manage Bitcoin, Ethereum, and other supported assets directly through your hardware wallet. Built-in portfolio view: Track your balances and asset distribution at a glance. Transaction details: Review fees, confirmations, and history with clarity. Coin control: Advanced users can select UTXOs for greater privacy and flexibility. Built-in exchange options: Access third-party exchange services from within Suite. Privacy-focused settings: Optional Tor integration enhances anonymity when connecting. Regular updates: New features, asset support, and security improvements released frequently. Why Use Trezor Suite? The combination of hardware wallet and dedicated app delivers a balance of usability and peace of mind. Unlike generic wallets or exchanges, Trezor Suite ensures that private keys never leave your Trezor device. You initiate transactions in Suite, but they are signed within the hardware wallet before broadcasting to the network. This design minimizes exposure to malware and phishing risks. Another advantage is the integration of tools you‚Äôd otherwise need multiple apps for. From portfolio tracking to secure exchanges and fee customization, everything is centralized within a single environment. How Trezor Suite Works Trezor Suite acts as a secure bridge between you and the blockchain. When you connect your Trezor device via USB, the Suite app recognizes it and allows you to interact with your wallets. You can view balances, generate new addresses, or prepare transactions. Each outgoing transaction must be reviewed and confirmed on the Trezor device itself, ensuring final approval always happens offline. The Suite does not store your keys. Instead, it communicates with the hardware wallet for cryptographic signing. This model keeps sensitive data isolated while giving you a familiar, intuitive interface. Getting Started with Trezor Suite Download and install: Visit the official Trezor website to download the latest desktop version for your operating system. Connect your Trezor device: Plug it in with the USB cable and launch the Suite app. Follow setup prompts: If this is your first time, create a new wallet, set up a PIN, and write down your recovery seed. Enable security features: Activate passphrase protection and update firmware if recommended. Explore the dashboard: Add accounts, check balances, and configure settings according to your needs. Privacy and Security Options Trezor Suite is built with user privacy in mind. One notable option is Tor integration, which helps hide your network traffic from surveillance. You can also adjust your transaction fee strategy, use coin control for Bitcoin, and connect to your own node for full sovereignty. Together, these tools make it easier to manage your crypto in a way that aligns with your privacy goals. Trezor Suite vs. Third-Party Wallets While Trezor devices are compatible with some external wallets, using Trezor Suite ensures seamless updates, full compatibility, and the highest trust in the software stack. Third-party apps may add features but can also introduce risks. Suite is designed as the default, most secure environment for Trezor users. Who Should Use Trezor Suite? Trezor Suite is for anyone using a Trezor hardware wallet, from casual Bitcoin savers to advanced crypto enthusiasts. Beginners benefit from its clean design and guided setup, while advanced users enjoy features like UTXO control, custom fees, and Tor support. If you want both security and usability in your daily crypto management, Suite is an essential tool. FAQs Is Trezor Suite free? Yes. The software is provided free of charge and is updated regularly by SatoshiLabs. Do I need internet access to use Suite? Yes, for viewing balances and broadcasting transactions. However, all signing occurs offline on your Trezor device. Can I use Suite without a hardware wallet? While you can explore some features, most functions require connecting a Trezor Model One or Model T. Start Using Trezor Suite Today If you already own a Trezor wallet, downloading Trezor Suite is the next step toward safer crypto management. Explore its features, take control of your privacy, and enjoy peace of mind knowing your private keys never leave your device. All trademarks belong to their respective owners. This content is for educational purposes only.
